<p>When building/designing a home from scratch.. Does it make sense to wire a home for &#8216;mostly&#8217; DC? (With the exception of power for major appliances)</p>
<p>Besides the usual argument I hear (resale issues).. is it worth it from an efficiency standpoint? (transmission loss of wires vs. conversion loss DC-&gt;AC)</p>
<p>The assumption is that your PRIMARY energy source is DC (solar) not AC (grid).</p>
